The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Sasken Communication Technologies Ltd (Sasken) has announced the results for the fourth quarter and full-year ended March 31. The consolidated revenues for the year stood at Rs 308.13 crore, compared with Rs 241.77 crore last year, registering a growth of 27%. Profit after tax for the full-year stood at Rs 22.92 crore after an exceptional item, compared with Rs 22.78 crore for the full year last year, registering a growth of 1%. The PAT for fiscal 2006 before the exceptional item was Rs. 29.68 Crore, a growth of 30% over last year

 ABG Shipyard Ltd will raise $100 million through issue of securities in the domestic or international markets to fund its expansion plans. The company board has approved the issue in global depository receipts (GDRs), American depository receipts (ADRs) and other securities convertible to equity shares of the company.

 Shree Cement has expanded its capacity by setting up a 2 million tonnes per annum capacity cement grinding unit at Khushkhera, near Gurgaon. The project would involve an investment of about Rs.100 crore and is expected to be completed by June 2007. 

 Larsen amp; Toubro Limited (L amp;T) has bagged an engineer-procure-construct contract valued at Rs. 581 crore from Kuwait Aviation Fuelling Company for its new fuel depot project at Kuwait International Airport. The project has to be completed in 24 months. 

 Thermax Ltd?s boiler and heater group has bagged an order worth Rs 360 crore from a leading business house for a their refinery project. The order entails design, manufacture, supply, construction and commissioning of auxiliary boilers and heat recovery stem generator.

 Venus Remedies will raise $12 million through the issue of foreign currency convertible bonds (FCCBs) in the international market. The FCCB offer also includes a green shoe option of $2 million and shall be listed on the Luxembourg Stock Exchange.

 HOV Services intends to enter the capital market with an initial public offering. The company will offer 4,05,0000 equity shares of face value Rs 10 each through a 100 per cent book-building process. The IPO arrangement was accompanied by filing its draft red herring prospectus with Sebi.

 Rallis India Ltd has reported a profit before tax of Rs 44.54 crore, which is 30 per cent higher than that of the previous year. The net profit after tax grew to Rs 42. 53 crore.

 GlaxoSmithKline Consumer Healthcare has introduced ENO Pudina in select Indian markets. 

